text: “LinkedIn is not immune to the effects of the global pandemic.” CEO Ryan Roslansky said the tech company will lay off 960 employees, roughly 6% of its workforce. https://t.co/z5NfK6OpsM

text: “If day after day, you’re waking up and dealing with patients that are extremely ill, some of whom wind up in the ICU and dying, it just takes a cumulative toll on our anxiety and burnout." https://t.co/i34tONeQc3

name: sfchronicle
text: Parts of S.F.'s plan for taller and denser housing around the intersection of Market Street and Van Ness Avenue will be put on pause, with members of the Board of Supervisors calling for a study on how the rezoning would impact communities of color. https://t.co/JpdJVQIGbB

text:

name: sfchronicle
text:
Navy report details final days of sailor who contracted the coronavirus: Charles Robert Thacker Jr. died of severe anoxic brain injury, cardiac arrest and COVID-19 sepsis. 

Read our exclusive story from @MGafni: https://t.co/xVNCP4aqg8

name: sfchronicle
text:
Ramón Laureano is in the A’s lineup in center field tonight against the Giants after being held out of Monday’s exhibition game with a tight calf.

https://t.co/Nr8yx7xIAD

name: sfchronicle
text:
The A’s expect to be without rookie left-hander A.J. Puk for at least the first two weeks of the season and possibly longer. Manager Bob Melvin said they don’t have a timetable for his potential return and said the team is “not going to push him.”

https://t.co/L0dz7HArgP

name: sfchronicle
text:
S.F. congressional candidate Shahid Buttar, Nancy Pelosi's election opponent, has been accused of repeated sexual harassment by a woman who says she's known him for nearly 20 years.   

Story by @Joegarofoli: https://t.co/pSZhAToMew

name: sfchronicle
text:
National Weather Service issues a red flag warning for part of northeastern California and western Nevada through Wednesday evening because gusty winds, low humidity and thunderstorms may create conditions for high fire danger.

Story by @ByLHernandez: https://t.co/fYl9jw92NF

name: sfchronicle
text: “Radioactive,” a movie about the life of scientist Marie Curie, will be available to stream starting Friday, July 24. https://t.co/InhomkVUHv

name: sfchronicle
text: Every year in the United States, there are 2.8 million antibiotic-resistant infections and more than 35,000 deaths as a result, according to the CDC. https://t.co/iKpFNCW0ai

name: sfchronicle
text: The number of COVID-19 patients in California surges past 7,000 for the first time on Monday, hitting a new record of 7,091 patients. https://t.co/NOtdGITPgL
